'''Mohammad Irfan Ismail''' (born 20 September 1988) is a Pakistani [[cricket]]er who has played {{Cric FC}} matches for [[Quetta cricket team|Quetta]] and {{Cric LO}} matches for the [[Quetta Bears]].

From [[Quetta]], a city in [[Balochistan, Pakistan|Balochistan]],<ref name="ca">[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/115/115522/115522.html Irfan Ismail] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> Irfan played inter-district matches for the Quetta under-19s from 2006, graduating to the [[Quetta District]] senior side in 2008.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/115/115522/Miscellaneous_Matches.html Miscellaneous matches played by Irfan Ismail (18)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> He made his limited-overs debut for the Quetta Bears franchise in March 2008, during the 2007<U+2013>08 season of the [[National One-day Championship|ABN-AMRO Cup]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/115/115522/List_A_Matches.html List A matches played by Irfan Ismail (4)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> A [[Left arm orthodox spin|left-arm orthodox]] spinner and left-handed lower-order [[batsman]], Irfan took three wickets from four matches at the tournament,<ref name="ca"/> with his best figures, 2/37 from 9.1 overs, coming against the [[Lahore Lions]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/166/166089.html Lahore Lions v Quetta Bears], ABN-AMRO Cup 2007/08 (Group A) <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref>

Irfan made his first-class debut for Quetta the following season, against the [[Karachi Blues]] in the [[Quaid-i-Azam Trophy]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/115/115522/First-Class_Matches.html First-class matches played by Irfan Ismail (2)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref> He took only a single wicket on debut, and in the next game (his last), against [[Multan cricket team|Multan]], he went wicketless. He consequently has a first-class average of 135.00.<ref name="ca"/> [[Irfan Ismail (cricketer, born 1992)|Mohammad Irfan Ismail (born 1992)]], another left-arm orthodox-spinner, also made a first-class appearance for Quetta during the 2008<U+2013>09 season. To avoid confusion, Irfan Ismail (born 1988), the subject of this article, is sometimes referred to as "Irfan Ismail, Sr.", while Irfan Ismail (born 1992) is sometimes referred to as "Irfan Ismail, Jr.".<ref>(22 December 2008). [http://www.dawn.com/news/335311/regional-squads-named-for-quaid-trophy "Regional squads named for Quaid Trophy"] <U+2013> Dawn.com. Retrieved 16 December 2014.</ref>

